Co-founded by David Matlin and Mark Patterson, MatlinPatterson is a leading global alternative asset manager with a focus on distressed and other credit opportunities. At the core of the organization’s investment programs are rigorous, disciplined, bottom-up fundamental credit research and analysis. MatlinPatterson’s investment professionals have decades of trading and investment experience in credit and have successfully executed investment strategies in investment partnerships and managed account structures. The firm is headquartered in New York.













